response: "Why does everyone expect me to be perfect? It feels like I'm suffocating under the weight of society's expectations."
"I'm starting to question my own sanity. Am I the only one who feels this overwhelming pressure to be flawless?"
"No matter what I do, it's never enough. I'm constantly chasing an unattainable standard of perfection."
"I feel like I'm losing touch with reality. The pressure to be perfect is driving me to the edge."
"I'm exhausted from pretending to have it all together. It's like I'm living in a never-ending performance."
